                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The mymnian attempts a claw Strike. If it hits, it deals no damage—instead, the mymnian's claws hook onto the target's soul and, for a moment, tug it out of the body so that the victim can catch a glimpse of how it will look after it dies. The target takes @Damage[5d8[mental]] damage with a @Check[will|dc:33|options:damaging-effect,inflicts:frightened] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes full damage and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target takes double damage and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2}.</p>"
